sentences:
Camp Caves was a US Army training camp north of the city of Rockhampton , Queensland , Australia .
Built during World War Two , the camp was in use from September 1943 until early in 1944 .
It was one of a number of US training camps in the area including Camp Nerimbera , Camp Thompson ’s Point , Camp Keppel Sands , Camp Yeppoon and Camp Wallaroo .
Camp Caves was the camp for the 24th Infantry Division , which was also called the Hawaiian Division .
It was called Camp Caves after the small town , The Caves , which was close to the campsite .
The site was along the side of the Bruce Highway .
It included medical services , warehouses , ammunition dumps , landing strips , and a small arms firing range .
Work on building the camp began in November 1942 but was soon stopped .
It started again in July 1943 .
The camp was no longer used after March 1944 .
